[{"id":"VR803935","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three parallel horizontal wires, each separated by a distance d. The bottom wire carries current I to the right, and a point P is a distance d below the wire. The middle wire carries current 2 I to the left. The top wire carries current 3 I to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803935.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three wires, each carrying a different current, are arranged as shown. The wires are each separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span>. The bottom wire is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> from Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>. What is the magnitude of the magnetic field at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span> due to the three wires?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803935_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Zero</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator mu sub 0, end sub, times I, and denominator 2 pi d\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator mu sub 0, end sub, times I, and denominator 2 pi d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=